2022-01-19 21:47:26	topcat001	But now I have perfect frame accurate hardware decoded video playback on Linux (with a TV/monitor which supports the correct refresh rates).
2022-01-19 21:48:07	topcat001	archdemon: The first step is to set up vaapi correctly. Then firefox 96 has a setting for vaapi which needs to be enabled.
2022-01-19 21:48:35	topcat001	It's all documented in various Arch wiki pages and linked from the hardware video aceel page.
2022-01-19 21:48:44	topcat001	So I can't claim any credit haha
2022-01-19 21:48:48	-->	heat_ [heat] (realname) (~heat@sortix/contributor/heat) has joined #archlinux
2022-01-19 21:48:57	<--	rassawyer (~rassawyer@c-73-175-191-186.hsd1.pa.comcast.net) has quit (Ping timeout: 240 seconds)
2022-01-19 21:48:59	<--	markpash (~markpash@51.15.69.81) has quit (Read error: Connection reset by peer)
